topic.title: Tachometer Command

body.p: The Tachometer Command (MRPC TACH Command) is used to monitor the speed of fans controlled by the switch.
These subcommands allow you to read and write to the tachometer hardware.

topic.title: Tachometer—Get Configuration TACH Sub-Command

body.p: The Get Configuration Sub-command is used to read the configuration from tachometer hardware.

section.title: Get Configuration TACH Sub-Command Input Data
section.p: The following table provides the input data for Get Configuration TACH Sub-Command:

table.title: Get Configuration TACH Sub-Command Input Data

section.p: This field must be set to 0 to perform a Get Configuration operation.
This field specifies the indexed channel (0 - 7) of the fan.

section.title: Get Configuration TACH Command Output Data
section.p: The following table provides the output data for Get Configuration TACH Sub-Command:

table.title: Get Configuration TACH Sub-Command Output Data
Get Configuration TACH Sub-Command Output Data

section.p: This is set to 0 for a get configuration response.
This field indicates the indexed channel (0 - 7) of the fan.
This field indicates whether the tachometer hardware is enabled or not.

table.title: Get Configuration TACH Sub-Command Hardware Enable Data

entry.p: The tachometer monitoring functionality is disabled.
The tachometer monitoring functionality is enabled.

section.p: This field indicates whether the tachometer counter of the channel will decrement on a falling or rising edge of the tachometer input pulse.

table.title: Get Configuration TACH Sub-Command Invert Edge Data

entry.p: The tachometer counter of the channel will decrement on a falling edge of the tachometer input pulse.
The tachometer counter of the channel will decrement on a rising edge of the tachometer input pulse

section.p: The field gets the LOW RPM (Revolutions/Minute) of the fan.
The field gets the HIGH RPM (Revolutions/Minute) of the fan.
The field gets the states of the fan. This command will clear all the states.

table.title: Get Configuration TACH Sub-Command Fan States Data

entry.p: Low-Thresh Interrupt state is set to 1 when the fan speed decrements below programmed low RPM value.
High-limit Interrupt state is set to 1 when the fan speed is greater than programmed high RPM value.
Count-fix interrupt is set to 1 when the fan speed is 0

topic.title: Tachometer—Set Configuration TACH Sub-Command

section.title: Set Configuration TACH Sub-Command Input Data
section.p: The Set Configuration TACH Sub-command is used to write the configuration to the tachometer hardware.

table.title: Set Configuration TACH Sub-Command Input Data
Set Configuration TACH Sub-Command Input Data

section.p: This field must be set to 1 to perform a Set Configuration operation.
This field specifies the indexed channel (0 - 7) of the fan.
This field is used in enabling or disabling the tachometer hardware.

table.title: Set Configuration TACH Sub-Command Hardware Enable Data

entry.p: The tachometer monitoring functionality is disabled.
The tachometer monitoring functionality is enabled.

section.p: This field is used to set the tachometer counter of the channel to decrement on a falling or rising edge of the tachometer input pulse.

table.title: Set ConfigurationTACH Sub-Command Invert Edge Data

entry.p: The tachometer counter of the channel will decrement on a falling edge of the tachometer input pulse.
The tachometer counter of the channel will decrement on a rising edge of the tachometer input pulse

section.p: The field is used to set the Low RPM (Revolutions/Minute) of the fan. The valid value range is 34 - 2200000.
The field is used to sets the High RPM (Revolutions/Minute) of the fan. The valid value range is 34 - 2200000.
When setting an invalid value for Low RPM and/or High RPM, this field returns a value of 0x00057007 to indicate an invalid RPM number.

table.title: Return Values for Invalid Low RPM and/or High RPM Values

entry.p: Invalid RPM value. The valid range is 34 - 2200000
